{"user_message": {"title": "Code Review — APPROVE — ai-bookkeeper b510ec9 (ADR-0006 home-nav e2e guard)", "content": "## Code Review — `ai-bookkeeper` @ `b510ec9`\n\n**Scope:** This run was triggered by a *backlog-scan* handoff that implemented no code (working tree holds only two untracked ADR docs). With no proposed PR to gate, I reviewed the **latest landed changeset** — `b510ec9` *test(e2e): add home-nav regression guard [ADR-0006]* — which post-dates my last review (`12bc223`/ADR 0004). Test-only change: `e2e/home-nav.spec.ts` (+45, new file). `page.tsx` untouched.\n\n### Verdict: ✅ **APPROVE** — 0 critical · 0 high · 0 medium · 2 low (non-gating)\n\n---\n\n### Security\nNothing to flag. Pure Playwright spec — no auth, injection, secret, or data-flow surface. N/A.\n\n### Correctness — all assumptions verified empirically, spec runs green\n- `e2e/home-nav.spec.ts:30` — brand-link selector `getByRole('link', {name: /Ledgerline/}).first()` — **verified**: header brand link is a real `next/link` (`src/app/page.tsx:13` `<Link href=\"/\">`; on `/pricing` at `pricing/page.tsx:360`), accessible name carries \"Ledgerline\" (text + image alt). Footer \"Ledgerline\" is a non-link `<span>` (`pricing/page.tsx:429`), so it can't be mis-selected; `.first()` additionally pins the DOM-first header link and avoids a strict-mode violation. ✓\n- `home-nav.spec.ts:22-40` — `__noReload` window-flag technique correctly distinguishes client-side `next/link` navigation (flag survives) from a full document reload (flag cleared). Sound and deterministic. ✓\n- `home-nav.spec.ts:43` — `getByRole('heading', {level: 1})` — **verified**: home renders an `<h1>` (`src/app/page.tsx:84`). Target route `/pricing` exists (`src/app/pricing/page.tsx`). ✓\n- **Gate re-run (reviewer value-add):** `eslint .` → 0 · `tsc --noEmit` → 0 · `npx playwright test e2e/home-nav.spec.ts` → **1 passed (4.6s)**. Matches the commit's claimed validation.\n- **Build-integrity check:** spec imports only `@playwright/test` — no barrel / untracked-sibling trap (contrast ADR-0002 `b29eeaa`). Clean.\n\n### Quality / Low (non-gating)\n- **L1 — `home-nav.spec.ts:30` (optional robustness):** brand-link targeting leans on the accessible-name regex `/Ledgerline/` + `.first()`. Works today, but is implicit — if a future header/footer adds another \"Ledgerline\"-named link above it in the DOM, `.first()` could drift. *Fix:* add `data-testid=\"brand-home\"` (or `aria-label=\"Ledgerline home\"`) to the header `<Link href=\"/\">` and select on that. Cheap hardening; not required to merge.\n- **L2 — ADJACENT / out-of-domain (NOT a finding against this changeset):** running the spec surfaced a Next.js console warning — *Image with src \"/brand/logo.png\" has width or height modified but not the other*. Origin is `src/app/page.tsx` / `pricing/page.tsx` (the brand `<Image width={28} height={28}>` + CSS sizing), **pre-existing**, unrelated to this test. Worth a separate housekeeping ticket (`className=\"h-auto\"` or matching CSS); does not gate this review.\n\n---\n\n**Closed / not re-flagged:** the `@next/next/no-html-link-for-pages` blocker on `page.tsx` that gated two prior ledger work orders is **resolved** (`page.tsx:13` uses `<Link>`, `eslint .` exits 0) — confirmed, not re-raised. This commit is precisely the behavioral guard locking that fix in.\n\n**Note:** the upstream backlog scan's triage gate (BL-0005 money-formatting consolidation, BL-HK1 commit ADR docs) is its own decision surface — out of scope for this review and not duplicated here. The shared Obsidian vault tools were not reachable in this run's environment, so this verdict is recorded in persona memory rather than the team graph.", "content_type": "success", "priority": "normal"}}

